topic.title: Get Partition Info Command

body.p: MRPC Command ID: 0x2B
The Get Partition Info command is used to get firmware flash layout and partitions' meta-data from the board.
There are two sub commands:

ul.li: 0x0 – Get the whole flash partition info
0x1 – get the meta-data info for a specified flash partition

body.p: The sub-commands share a set of MRPC Command Return Values, refer to table_MRPC_Command_common_Return_Value of MRPC Command Return Value (0x808)Memory Mapped Remote Procedure Calls (MRPC)

topic.title: Get Partition Info - Get All Info Sub-Command

body.p: The sub-command is used to get the flash layout info, active partition info as well as running partition info.

table.title: Get Partition Info Sub-Command -Get All Info Input Data

body.p: Specifies the Sub-Command for Get Partition Info MRPC command. Set to 0x0 for the Get All Info operation.
Specifies the output structure for the sub-command.

table.title: Get Partition Info Sub-Command -Get All Info Output Data

entry.p: flash partition info for Partition Map 0
flash partition info for Partition Map 1
flash partition info for Configuration File 0
flash partition info for Configuration File 1

row.entry: flash partition info for Firmware Image 0

entry.p: flash partition info for Firmware Image 1
flash partition info for Non-Volatile Log
flash partition info for Vendor 0 partition
flash partition info for Vendor 7 partition

body.p: The image CRC/length/version/valid/active fields are reserved for NVlog partition and vendor x partitions.Image active field is also reserved for bootloader partition.
is_using : a flag to check a partition is in using state or not. 0x1 - the partition is in using state; 0x0 - the partition isn't in using state.

topic.title: Get Partition Info - Get meta-data Sub-Command

body.p: The get meta-data sub-command is used to get the meta-data for a specified flash partition.

table.title: Get Partition Info sub-command get meta-data Input Data

body.p: Specifies the Get Partition Info Sub-Command. Set to 0x1 for the Get meta-data operation.
Specifies the flash partition ID. The valid partition id is listed as below:
0: Bootloader1 partition ID
1: Bootloader2 Partition0 ID
2: Bootloader2 Partition1 ID
3: PartitonMap Partition0 ID
4: PartitonMap Partition1 ID
5: Configure file Partition0 ID
6: Configure file Partition1 ID
7: Main Firmware Partition0 ID
8: Main Firmware Partition1 ID

Specifies the output structure for the sub-command. The data structure is just meta-data, which totally has 256 bytes for a specified valid flash partition, refer to the table<Flash Partition Meta-data>#trident_flash_partition_map/table_Flash_Partition_Metadata Table 1
